<br>
One of my best EQ friends is a cleric.  We are both lvl 54, with one of us about to hit lvl 55.  The wyverns are easy, but seems like theres lots of competition for spawns and xp not that good since some wyverns are turning green.<br>
<br>
I am looking for some ideas where she and I could hunt and get some decent xp.  I wonder if raptors would be a good choice, knowing that they are usually camped and that it takes a while to get to raptor island (I can cast absconb &lt;sp&gt; on myself but cannot cast it on anyone else).<br>
<br>
Any suggestions would be appreciated for a wizard/cleric combo.  Thanks.<br>
 <p>Dracomin Spidernooker<BR>
Level 54 Wizard<BR>
<BR>
Spooch<BR>
Level 19 Cleric<BR>


</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uwolandgrauensturm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Woland Grauensturm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/13/01 12:09:36 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Teaming up with a cleric</span><hr size=1> Cleric + wiz is a bad combination. You could snare / fear but that wouldn't drastically improve your kill rate. <br>
<br>
I'd suggest that you grab a tank to pull and tank for you. It will be easier for you to stay at one place and you can meditate while the tank does his/her thing.<br>
<br>
 <p><BR>
<p align="center"><img border="0" src="http://hem.passagen.se/stigard/eqpics/allchars.jpg" width="480" height="120"></p>
<p align="center"><font face="Arial" size="2">Woland - SHD - Ayda - WIZ - Mirixia - CLR - Zarloth - NEC</font></p>
<BR>

</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uspace78.showPublicProfile?language=EN>space78</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/13/01 9:27:28 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Teaming up with a cleric</span><hr size=1> cleric + wiz bad combo??? not hardly<br>
tell the clerics to load up the stuns and go to work with your nukes. i grpd with a cleric in from 30-50 off and on and still do on occasion, when the cleric is free (grps seem to snatch the clerics rather fast)<br>
a wiz/cleric could easily take down damn near anything in bw, cleric stuns sarnaks while u nuke em into the ground, its a great combo imo. <br>
since i have jboots i would rather have a cleric partner than a druid, the only thing to make me think twice bout that is druid tracking hehe <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uqaman.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Qaman</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/13/01 9:36:21 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Teaming up with a cleric</span><hr size=1> Post 50, a cleric is not the best choice for a combo team really. You do get a few more choices though since you can fear kite in SF if you want.<br>
<br>
&gt;a wiz/cleric could easily take down damn near anything in bw, cleric stuns sarnaks while u nuke em into the ground, its a great combo imo. <br>
<br>
A wiz solo can take down most anything in BW that doesn't summon (and 4 of them at a time too) except gullerbacks pretty much. And having a cleric won't help too much with them. <p>Qaman<BR>
Sorcerer<BR>
Ayonae Ro</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uspace78.showPublicProfile?language=EN>space78</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/13/01 12:56:51 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Teaming up with a cleric</span><hr size=1> until lvl 54 i couldnt take scor hornets and other 45+ mobs, to many resists, with a cleric or any other class for that matter its possible. clerics still make good partners post 50. btw even at 56 i still have a hard time with higher lvl wurms, much less quadding them hehe <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uqaman.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Qaman</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/13/01 2:02:43 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Teaming up with a cleric</span><hr size=1> True, but wurms are a waste of time anyways for xp. Not sure why you were having probs with the others before 54, I never had many probs with them when I was doin BW. Not sure what a cleric is buying you post 50 though. Really, most classes would be more help unless you are planning on getting hit a lot. It doesn't really speed up your killing at all, which means you are basically halving your xp. If you want someplace that they might be useful, I'd prolly lean more towards right inside the entrance to Chardok, but in BW one would just slow ya down. <p>Qaman<BR>
Sorcerer<BR>
Ayonae Ro</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uspace78.showPublicProfile?language=EN>space78</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/13/01 6:02:06 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Teaming up with a cleric</span><hr size=1> it was just an example, ok so a poor one at that hehe, however clerics come in pretty handy for caster mobs.<br>
no one could understand why i couldnt solo in bw, i have 200 int, 350+ mana on items, just always ran oom, to many resists until 54 for some reason, cept on the greenies hehe, was quite annoying<br>
<br>
and sometimes halving ur xp is worth the added security, and in the off chance that you did perish, wow a cleric right there <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showMessage?topicID=104.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showMessage?topicID=93.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.emailToFriend?topicID=97.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.threadControl?topicID=97.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=97.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=97.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub23.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm1">General Discussion<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm3">Trade Forum<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm4">Rant Forum<option value="gra